data.chText: 清晰的；清楚的；明白的；明显的
data.enText: easily or clearly heard, seen, felt, etc.
There was a distinct smell of gas.

data.chText: 他说话声音不大，但字字清晰。
data.enText: His voice was quiet but every word was distinct.

data.chText: 截然不同的；有区别的；不同种类的
data.enText: clearly different or of a different kind

data.chText: 调查结果分为截然不同的两组。
data.enText: The results of the survey fell into two distinct groups.

data.chText: 牙买加的雷盖音乐完全不同于北美的爵士乐或布鲁斯音乐。
data.enText: Jamaican reggae music is quite distinct from North American jazz or blues.

data.chText: 完全不同于大城市的农村地区
data.enText: rural areas, as distinct from major cities

data.chText: 确定无疑的；确实的；确切的
data.enText: used to emphasize that you think an idea or situation definitely exists and is important

data.chText: 托尼个子高是个明显的优势。
data.enText: Being tall gave Tony a distinct advantage.

data.chText: 我确实感到有人在监视我。
data.enText: I had the distinct impression I was being watched.

data.chText: 目前罢工确有可能发生。
data.enText: A strike is now a distinct possibility.

data.chText: 我清楚地听到有人在叫我。
data.enText: I distinctly heard someone calling me.

data.chText: 他什么事都能记得清清楚楚。
data.enText: He could remember everything very distinctly.

simple_means.memory_skill: dis 分开 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 → 把刺分开后显得清楚的；明显的 → 清楚的；明显的

ex.chText: 她要求我给出一个明确的答复。
ex.enText: She demanded I give a definite answer.

ex.chText: 有必要为你的论文提交定一个确切的日期。
ex.enText: It is necessary to fix a definite date for the submission of your paper.

ex.chText: 人们明显地感觉到情况越来越好。
ex.enText: There was a definite feeling that things were getting better.

synonyms.bx: 指答复、安排等明确肯定、不会改变的；也可指事物显而易见的。

ex.chText: 房间里有一股明显的烟味。
ex.enText: There is a distinct smell of cigarettes in the room.

ex.chText: 那栋大厦的轮廓变得清晰了。
ex.enText: The outline of the building became distinct.

synonyms.bx: 指可以清楚地看到、听到或闻到的。

ex.enText: It was evident that she was excited.

ex.chText: 他十分清楚她没有说真实的年龄。
ex.enText: It was evident to him that she was lying about her age.

ex.chText: 他所做的一切都清楚地表明他爱这个姑娘。
ex.enText: His love for the girl was evident in all that he did.

ex.chText: 患病期间哈里表现出的勇气我们大家有目共睹。
ex.enText: Harry's courage during his illness was evident to all of us.

ex.chText: 很显然，将会有一些人失业。
ex.enText: It is evident that there will be some job losses.

synonyms.bx: 指根据事实显而易见的。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：明白的，明显的

tr: clearly or sharply defined to the mind
example: Claudius was the first to invade Britain with distinct...intentions of conquest
trenchant distinctions between right and wrong
the ship appeared as a distinct silhouette
the word `nationalism' is used in at least two distinct senses
a tree related to but quite distinct from the European beech
management had interests quite distinct from those of their employees

tr: constituting a separate entity or part
example: a government with three discrete divisions

value.def: If something is distinct from something else of the same type, it is different or separate from it.

example.ex: Engineering and technology are disciplines distinct from one another and from science...
example.tran: 工程学和工艺学互不相同，也有别于自然学科。

example.ex: This book is divided into two distinct parts.
example.tran: 这本书分为内容不同的两部分。

value.tran: 有区别的;不同的;个别的

example.ex: ...a banking industry with two distinctly different sectors.
example.tran: 涉足两个截然不同领域的银行业

value.def: If something is distinct, you can hear, see, or taste it clearly.

example.ex: ...to impart a distinct flavor with a minimum of cooking fat.
example.tran: 用最少量的食用油来调出一种独特的口味

example.ex: I distinctly heard the loudspeaker calling passengers for the Turin-Amsterdam flight.
example.tran: 我清楚地听到扩音器里在请都灵至阿姆斯特丹航班的旅客登机。

value.def: If an idea, thought, or intention is distinct, it is clear and definite.

example.ex: Now that Tony was no longer present, there was a distinct change in her attitude...
example.tran: 由于托尼不在场了，她的态度有了明显的转变。

example.ex: I have distinct memories of him in his last years.
example.tran: 我清楚地记得他最后几年的情况。

value.tran: 确定无疑的;确切的;清楚的

example.ex: I distinctly remember wishing I had not got involved.
example.tran: 我清楚地记得希望自己没有被牵扯进去。

value.def: You can use distinct to emphasize that something is great enough in amount or degree to be noticeable or important.

example.ex: Being 6ft 3in tall has some distinct disadvantages!
example.tran: 身高6英尺3英寸有些明显的不便之处！

example.ex: Another Cup marathon between the two sides is now a distinct possibility.
example.tran: 双方很可能再进行一场马拉松式的优胜杯比赛。

example.ex: His government is looking distinctly shaky.
example.tran: 他的政府显然正处于风雨飘摇之中。

value.def: If you say that you are talking about one thing as distinct from another, you are indicating exactly which thing you mean.

example.ex: There's a lot of evidence that oily fish, as distinct from fatty meat, has a beneficial effect.
example.tran: 有许多证据表明油性鱼，与高脂肪肉不同，对人体有益。

value.tran: 截然不同于;完全不同于;有区别于

trans: 位图索引对于相异基数；于相异基数

partsOfSpeech.dec: dis 分开 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 → 把刺分开后显得清楚的；明显的 → 清楚的；明显的
dis 分开 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 + ion，distinct 的名词 → 区别；优秀
dis 分开 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 + ive …的 → 有区别的；与众不同的
di〔s〕分离 + stingu 刺；刺激 + ish 使… → 把不同的刺分离 → 区别
distinguish 区别；辨出 + ed 表形容词 → 与众不同的 → 著名的
ex 出 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 → 拔出刺 → 灭绝的，注意：ex后接s开头的词根时省略s
extinct 灭绝的 + ion 表名词 → 灭绝
ex 出 + tingu 刺 + ish 使… → 把刺拔出，刺引申为火焰 → 熄灭
in 使… + stig〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 + ate 做，造成，使… → 刺激〔别人〕→ 煽动
in 向内 + stinct 刺；刺激 → 内在的刺激 → 本能
stimul 刺；刺激 + ate 做，造成，使… → 刺激，鼓励
stimul 刺；刺激 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 刺激，鼓励
sting 刺；刺激 + y …的 → 对钱的事挑刺 → 小气的
